  "Sarah wants to open a bakery. Her fixed costs are $5,000/month (rent, insurance, loan payment). Variable costs are $3 per item. She sells each item for $8. How many items must she sell per month to break even?": "",
  "625 items": "",
  "500 items": "",
  "1,000 items": "",
  "1,667 items": "",
  "Break-even = Fixed costs / (Price - Variable cost) = $5,000 / ($8 - $3) = $5,000 / $5 = 1,000 items per month. Below 1,000 items she loses money; above 1,000 she earns profit.": "",
